<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Regrets Education Minister's Resignation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302212794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1808 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302212794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
expressed great regret over the resignation of Education 
Minister Rainer Ortleb. Government spokesman Dieter Vogel said 
this evening that the chancellor had, however, expressed 
understanding for the health reasons "that forced Professor 
Ortleb to give up his ministerial office." In his three years 
as minister, Ortleb has played a major part in dealing with the 
changes in the education system that came about as a result of 
German unification. 
  In particular, he played a successful role in the renewal 
and 
rebuilding of the higher education system in the eastern states, 
the statement goes on to say. Ortleb has shown great commitment 
in introducing his experience and the concerns of the eastern 
states into the German Government's work. The chancellor 
thanked Ortleb for his achievements as a member of the cabinet 
and expressed the hope that he would continue to play a part in 
politics using his expertise and experience. 

</TEXT>

