<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Paris Urges UN To Consider Sanctions Against DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0302152894 Paris AFP in English 1455 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0302152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Paris, Feb 3 (AFP) -- The UN Security Council 
should consider imposing sanctions against North Korea for its 
continued refusal to allow inspections of its nuclear sites, the 
French Foreign Ministry said Wednesday [2 February]. 
  "We note that there has been no progress in discussions 
between the United States and North Korea concerning a 
resumption of inspections by the International Atomic Energy 
Agency (IAEA) and we think the issue of sanctions should be 
taken up before the Security Council," Foreign Ministry 
spokeswoman Catherine Colonna said. 
  Pyongyang, which is suspected of developing nuclear weapons, 
has been refusing to allow IAEA inspections of two key nuclear 
sites since last February, despite repeated international 
pressure. [passage omitted] 
  Although North Korean negotiators agreed last month in 
principle to allow the inspections, no accord has been reached 
on the terms of how the inspections will be carried out. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

