<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Balladur Stresses Government Will Help Fisherman </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402113994 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1000 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Leaving the Hotel de Ville in Rennes, Prime 
Minister Edouard Balladur announced that he will meet with 
representatives of the fishing industry. The minister for 
[agriculture and] fisheries said only that the meeting will 
probably take place in the late morning. Balladur went on to 
the Regional Council. [passage omitted] 
  At the beginning of his remarks, the prime minister of 
course 
started by mentioning the fishing dispute: 
  [Begin Balladur recording] Faced with this crisis, we are 
ready to use all means possible to come to the help of those who 
are threatened or let down by the evolution of the world and the 
evolution of society. We have already applied this principle in 
the farming sector. We are applying this same principle to 
industrial sectors which are in difficulty. I am resolved to 
apply the same principle also to the fishing sector, which, in 
its turn is also experiencing difficulties caused by many 
different factors. But, whatever the cause, the government 
intends to resolve problems which occur, and we will do for the 
fishing industry what we did for the farming industry. In other 
words, we will make sure that those involved in Brittany or 
elsewhere will have a better future to look forward to. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

