<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pope Receives Croatia's Granic, Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402131594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0402131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Andjelko Perincic report from the Vatican] </F>
  [Text] Pope John Paul II today received Mate Granic, the 
Croatian deputy prime minister and foreign minister, for a 
private audience. The meeting, held in the Pope's private 
library, lasted almost half an hour. At the end of the meeting 
the pope also received other members of the Croatian delegation, 
including Smiljana Sinac, assistant foreign minister, and Ivo 
Livljanic, ambassador of the Republic of Croatia to the Vatican, 
as well as a group of Croatian journalists who are covering 
minister Granic's visit to Rome. 
  It was learned from well-informed sources that during the 
meeting between the pope and Granic discussed the situation in 
our region, especially that of the Croats in the crisis areas, 
and a possible visit to Croatia by the pope. 
  After the meeting Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic was 
received in the Vatican by Vatican secretary of state Cardinal 
Angelo Sodano. 

</TEXT>

