<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economics Minister Rules Out More Aid for Steel </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0302130694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1132 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0302130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN)--Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt 
made it clear at a meeting with leading German steel industry 
representatives today in Bonn that the German steel industry 
cannot count on further government assistance. The budget 
situation left no scope for this. Rexrodt and the steel 
managers agreed that further capacity reductions "are possible 
only within the framework of an agreed upon, Europe-wide 
program." Moreover, close attention will have to be paid to the 
proper use of the subsidies for the steel industry in all EU 
countries, Rexrodt said. The EU subsidies could not be used to 
acquire new shares of the market. The crisis meeting was called 
by Rexrodt. The steel sector was represented by the executive 
boards of the steel concerns and German Steel Federation 
President Ruprecht Vondran. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

