<F P=102>  NC0302154694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0302154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Andreas Paraskhos] </F>
  [Excerpt] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said 
today that the final draft of the report on the 
confidence-building measures [CBM's] prepared by Cypriot 
Government experts answers the most important question raised 
when the term confidence-building measures was added to Cyprus' 
political dictionary. That question is: Will implementation of 
the CBM's mean the possibility of recognition, direct or 
indirect, of the Turkish Cypriot pseudostate? Kasoulidhis said 
that it appears, at last, that the CBM's can be implemented 
without the danger of recognition of the pseudostate. 
  [Begin Kasoulidhis recording] It appears that there are ways 
that can be agreed upon to implement the CBM's without the 
direct or indirect recognition of the pseudostate. 
  The foreign minister is expected to carry the final draft of 
the report with him when he returns from London tonight. The 
constitutional and legal processing of the report took place in 
London. [end recording] 
  The experts' report is currently in the hands of Foreign 
Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

