<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Receives Council of Europe Rapporteur </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0302155094 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1130 GMT 3 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0302155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lord Finsberg, rapporteur for the Cyprus problem at 
the Political Affairs Committee of the Council of Europe 
Parliamentary Assembly, has begun his contacts in the Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus. 
  President Rauf Denktas received Lord Finsberg this morning 
and conferred with him for some time. In a statement after the 
meeting, Denktas said that he discussed with Lord Finsberg, who 
is assessing the Cyprus situation, the problems created by the 
lack of Turkish Cypriot representation at the Council of Europe 
and their possible solutions. Denktas noted that he told Lord 
Finsberg how the obstacles created by the recognition of the 
Greek Cypriot administration as the legitimate government can be 
eliminated, adding that Lord Finsberg expressed the hope that 
these problems will be averted if progress is made on the 
confidence-building measures. Denktas said that the UN 
secretary general should send letters to both sides for the 
talks on the confidence-building measures to begin. He 
concluded by describing the recent positive statements made by 
the Greek Cypriot side as an optimistic development. 

</TEXT>

