<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas Said To Make New Demand on Varosha Return </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0302214894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2000 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0302214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas has demanded 
that the zone north of Dhimokratias Avenue be removed from the 
Varosha fenced-off area that will be placed under UN control and 
be replaced with an area of similar size south of the fenced-off 
area. According to Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation [CyBC] 
information, this was the evaluation of Robert Lamb, the U.S. 
State Department special coordinator on the Cyprus issue. Lamb 
met with President Glavkos Kliridhis today. 
  Based on CyBC information, Denktas' new demand concerns all 
services necessary to the operation of the area that will be 
returned, such as the Electricity Authority, the 
Telecommunications Authority, the Municipal Market, the 
warehouses, the packaging units, the Greek Famagusta High School 
and its library, the stadium, and many hotels. The same reports 
say that Lamb informed the Greek Cypriot side, which rejected 
the new demand. 
  The Greek Cypriot side also insisted that a date be set for 
the beginning of the second phase for the return of Varosha. 
The measures provide that the first phase will begin 18 months 
after the agreement is signed but do not determine the date for 
the beginning of the second phase. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

