<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Calls For 3-Point Ultimatum on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602175094 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602175094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A shell fired at a market in Sarajevo yesterday 
killed 68 and wounded 200. This carnage has provoked outrage 
everywhere and has already resulted in a response by NATO 
countries this afternoon. There were many contacts between 
capitals today, and it was decided to organize a NATO meeting as 
early as possible. France will call on its allies to serve an 
ultimatum on the belligerents in Bosnia, a three-point 
ultimatum. Let's listen to French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] First, the siege of Sarajevo must be 
lifted, this means that Serbian forces must pull back to a 
distance making the renewed shelling of the town materially 
impossible. Second, with a view to lifting this siege, heavy 
weapons held by Serbs and Bosnians within a range of 30 km 
around the town must be brought together and put under UN 
Protection Force control. This measure will be the first stage 
in setting up the UN administration over Sarajevo which is -- 
let me remind you -- a basic element of the European Union peace 
plan and which has been accepted in principle by all parties. 
Third, if these two conditions are not met within a short 
deadline to be set by the allies, all means, including air 
power, should be used to enforce them. [end recording] 
  [Announcer] This statement was made less than half an hour 
ago at the Quai d'Orsay and was recorded by Philippe Lefebvre. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-38648 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu025aa_94013" </HT>


