<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As defense minister I am able to confirm that our 
bases are ready to provide effective support, if and when NATO 
decides to intervene in Bosnia. The statement was made by 
Defense Minister Fabbio Fabbri, who was speaking about the 
latest developments in the Bosnian situation. 
  Fabbri stressed that, with UN authorization, air strikes 
could be directed against the main sources of fire and provide 
adequate air cover for the peacekeeping forces. The problem 
which so dramatically confronts our consciences, Fabbri said, is 
whether it is possible to stop the massacres in Sarajevo. 

