<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alternative National Service Law Adopted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0502170794 Salzburg SALZBURGER NACHRICHTEN in German 4 Feb 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU0502170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Salzburg SALZBURGER NACHRICHTEN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Nationalrat Decides on Longer </F>
Alternative National Service"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- By adopting the new law on alternative 
national service on Thursday [3 February], the Nationalrat drew 
a line under the months of debate about the duration of 
alternative national service. Retroactively as of 1 January, 
alternative national service will be extended from 10 to 11 
months; one month of that can be served through exercises. If 
more than 3,000 conscripts apply for alternative national 
service from May to October, this service will last 12 months as 
of next year. In the future, the young men doing alternative 
national service will no longer get cash for food and clothes, 
so that their income will go down from so far up to 8,000 
schillings per month to 3,000 schillings. In return, the 
monthly salary for men doing military service will be raised 
from 2,000 to 3,000 schillings. In addition, they are permitted 
to use public transport free of charge [when they are in 
uniform]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

