<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Van Baal Appointed UN Chief of Staff in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0402142594 Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT in Dutch 4 Feb 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> BR0402142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Dutch </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "General Van Baal Becomes UN Chief of </F>
Staff in Bosnia"] 
  [Excerpt] From 1 March onwards, the Netherlands will be 
represented in the top military command of the UN's 
Bosnia-Herzegovina forces. Brigadier General A. Van Baal has 
been appointed by Defense Minister Ter Beek to the position of 
command chief of staff, succeeding Ramsey from the United 
Kingdom. 
  Van Baal (47) will become second in command to British 
General Rose, UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] commander in 
Bosnia. After six months, another Dutchman will take over the 
position for another half year. Van Baal will be staying at the 
UNPROFOR headquarters at Kiseljak next weekend, to get 
acquainted with Rose, who recently succeeded General Briquemont 
from Belgium. 
  Van Baal, an artillerist, is currently commander of the 43rd 
mechanized brigade at Havelte. He has also been head of the 
army staff's organizational department in the Hague. Van Baal 
is regarded as a rising star within the army. 
  He will have the daily command of 460 troops of different 
nationalities, including 60 Dutchmen. From the headquarters in 
Kiseljak, the chief of staff will act as the deputy commander of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina command. 
  Together with the commander, he is in charge of the overall 
coordination of all troops in Bosnia. They frequently consult 
with political and military leaders from the contending parties, 
such as the Bosnian Serb leaders Karadzic and Mladic. 
  The command is also responsible for the protection of food 
convoys organized by the UNHCR (United Nations High Commissioner 
for Refugees). The Dutch-Belgian transportation battalion in 
Central Bosnia, the UNHCR's only military transportation unit, 
also comes under the command. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

