<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chancellor Kohl Addresses Security Conference </TI></H3>
<H4>   Rejects Military Intervention in Bosnia </H4>
<F P=102> LD0502105894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0947 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0502105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl 
rejects UN or NATO military intervention in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
I view proposals for seeking a solution through military 
strikes with a "great deal of skepticism," the chancellor said 
at a conference on security policy in Munich today. It is also 
difficult at present "to decide who is more culpable." 
  Kohl again warned the Croatian Government against further 
aggravating the civil war in the Balkans. He regretted that the 
Croatian Government had so far not made "the necessary public 
statements." Those who change borders by violent means cannot 
count on the Federal Republic to give aid for reconstruction 
after the war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-38671 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu025_h_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-025 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  7 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

