<H3> <TI>   Federal Office Watches Republikaner in Lower Saxony </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702123494 Hamburg DER SPIEGEL in German 7 Feb 94 p 53 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DER SPIEGEL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Watchers From Cologne"] </F>
  [Text] Lower Saxony's Republikaner are now being watched 
by the Federal Office for the Protection of the Constitution 
(BfV). This is the BfV's reaction to a court ruling that 
prohibited colleagues from the Lower Saxony Office for the 
Protection of the Constitution to watch Franz Schoenhuber's 
rightist-populist party. The background: The red-green Lower 
Saxony has a particularly restrictive constitutional protection 
law. According to the ruling, the Land Office may use 
intelligence service means against political parties only if 
these parties struggle against the Basic Law in a "militant and 
aggressive manner." The BfV is affected neither by the land law 
nor by the negative ruling. 

</TEXT>

