<H3> <TI>   Communications, Entertainment Firms Plan Pay Television </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402153094 Berlin DIE WELT in German 4 Feb 93 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> AU0402153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DIE WELT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Telekom, ZDF, Kirch, and Bertelsmann </F>
Establish Pay Television Station"] 
  [Text] Frankfurt/Main -- With the entertainment concern 
Bertelsmann AG, the Munich film trader Leo Kirch, the Multimedia 
Market, and ZDF, German Telekom wants to get into the growing 
pay television business. This was reported by Telekom Executive 
Board member Dieter Gallist. Telekom thinks that 19 million 
households in Germany are now "qualified for pay television" -- 
but only 5 percent are subscribers to pay television. The share 
is already 17 percent in France and 55 percent in England, it 
was stated. 

</TEXT>

