<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pakistan's Asif Ali Urges Assistance on Kashmir </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0502140594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0502140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has urged the UN Human Rights Commission 
to send a special committee to occupied Kashmir to assess the 
human rights violations committed by Indian troops there. This 
was stated by Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahamd Ali during his 
talks with his French counterpart, Alain Juppe, in Paris. The 
foreign minister handed over a message from Pakistan's prime 
minister to Alain Juppe, appealing for French assistance toward 
setting up a special committee. Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali explained 
Pakistan's efforts for establishing peace in South Asia, 
especially toward resolving the Kashmir issue. He also informed 
the French foreign minister of human rights violations and 
atrocities committed by Indian troops in occupied Kashmir. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

