<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Thanks Supporters, Stresses Unity </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602193794 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1848 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Studio interview with presidential candidate Martti </F>
Ahtisaari by unidentified reporter -- live] 
  [Excerpt] [Reporter] Martti Ahtissari, your words to the 
voters, both your own supporters and Elisabeth Rehn's supporters? 
  [Ahtisaari] Of course, first of all I would like to thank 
Elisabeth Rehn for a good and fair campaign. I think that is 
quite an essential factor, for which I want to thank Elisabeth 
Rehn. I also hope that the people who voted for Elisabeth Rehn 
can also give their support for me in these new and difficult 
tasks. At the same time, of course, I want to thank all those 
who have taken part in my campaign, thousands of volunteers in 
various parts of Finland. I am very grateful to all of them and 
to all of you, good friends. Without your work these elections 
would never have ended as they did. 
  [Reporter] The nation is not divided? 
  [Ahtisaari] I would say that the future president will face 
very difficult tasks, both in the economy, politics, 
internationally, and then it is important that the nation is not 
divided over these issues, and I will insure that I will be seen 
as the president of the entire country. This is the way I 
intend to take things forward. In fact, during my entire 
campaign I have stressed that the Finnish nation must not be 
divided over these issues. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

