<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Officer Killed in 6 Feb Somalia Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602182594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1740 GMT 
6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Italian officer, Lieutenant Giulio Ruzzi, 29, was 
killed today in Somalia. A soldier from the same Italian 
contingent, Franco Ratenni, 22, was seriously injured. 
  According to information from the Defense Ministry, a column 
from the Italian contingent, UNOSOM [UN Operation in Somalia] 2, 
which was on its way from Bulo Burti to Balad carrying food, was 
attacked by a hail of bullets at 1700. Lieutenant Ruzzi died 
while being transported to the hospital in Giohar. 

</TEXT>

