<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Speaker Urges End to Somalia Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702122294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1142 GMT 
7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Giovanni Spadolini said: I think that the mission in 
Somalia must absolutely be brought to an end. 
  Spadolini, who is in Cote d'Ivoire for Houphouet-Boigny's 
funeral, told journalists that Italy can only try and safeguard 
its security and interests while supporting a UN solution. 
  He added: We did not particularly want to go there, we made 
great efforts, and more than 10 of our people were killed. 

</TEXT>

