<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demirel Urges Air Operation for Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0602115794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0602115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still photograph of President </F>
Demirel] 
  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has said that the heavy 
weapons of those besieging Sarajevo must be silenced with an air 
operation within the framework of the UN and NATO resolutions, 
and that effective measures must be taken to lift the siege. 
  In a message he sent to Bosnia-Herzegovina President Alija 
Izetbegovic, Demirel expressed his deep regret over the 
horrendous attack in Sarajevo. He said: This recent attack 
shows once again that the time has come and gone for the 
civilized world and for the international organizations that 
represent it to fulfill their responsibilities. I call on the 
civilized world once again to silence with an air operation -- 
within the framework of the UN and NATO resolutions -- the heavy 
weapons of those forces mercilessly besieging Sarajevo as soon 
as possible, and to take effective measures to lift this siege. 
I am conveying our demands regarding this issue with messages 
to the concerned international organizations and to the leaders 
of the leading countries of the world. 
  I extend Turkey's and my own personal condolences to the 
people of Bosnia-Herzegovina for those killed in this despicable 
attack. I affirm that, as always, Turkey is on the side of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and is ready to extend to it every kind of 
support. 
  Taking this opportunity, I extend my deepest respects. 

</TEXT>

