<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Criticizes Sarajevo Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0602195694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0602195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpts] Murat Karayalcin, leader of the Social 
Democratic Populist Party, state minister, and deputy prime 
minister, addressed the people in Corum, where he presented 460 
land deeds within the framework of the redevelopment and 
renovation plan. [passage omitted] 
  On the subject of the massacre the Serbs perpetrated on 
Sarajevo yesterday, Karayalcin severely condemned the approach 
of the United States and European countries on the issue. 
Explaining that the above countries were silently watching the 
massacre of 68 people in Sarajevo, Karayalcin recalled that 
these same countries sent troops when faced with the slightest 
disagreement in the Middle East. Karayalcin said: 
  [Begin Karayalcin recording] We are against Islamic 
radicalism. We refuse to recognize Islamic radicalism and 
regimes that are not secular. As Turkish republicans, we are 
against all attacks against laicism; but while we, on the one 
hand, reject Muslim initiatives that are not secular, we cannot, 
on the other hand, accept or stomach Christian radicalism. I 
would like to ask you dear citizens of Corum, if the world would 
be as silent as it is now if the inhabitants of Sarajevo were 
not Muslims or if they were Jews instead of Muslims. [end 
recording] 
  Karayalcin further stated that the countries that are not 
intervening in Sarajevo should at least extend military aid to 
the Muslims living there. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

