<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mock Views EU Sanctions on Croatia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0402130094 Salzburg SALZBURGER NACHRICHTEN ZEITUNG in 
German 4 Feb 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU0402130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Salzburg SALZBURGER NACHRICHTEN ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "hhs": "Mock: Vienna To Examine EU Decision"] </F>
  [Text] Should the European Union [EU] agree on sanctions 
against Croatia next Monday, Vienna will probably go along with 
this decision, Foreign Minister Alois Mock indicated in Brussels 
on Thursday [3 February]. 
  The foreign minister was inquiring about the chances of 
completing the entry talks by the end of February. The planned 
conclusion of the negotiations with the four membership 
candidates will be the subject of a meeting between the 12 EU 
and the four EFTA [European Free Trade Association] foreign 
ministers, who will meet in Brussels on Monday. In view of the 
increasingly overt Croatian attacks against Muslims in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, they will also discuss imposing sanctions 
against Zagreb, comparable with those against Serbia. 

</TEXT>

