<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Says Croatian Troops in Bosnia `Scandal' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402145294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1420 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
strongly criticized Croatia because of reports on the 
involvement of regular Croatian soldiers in the war in 
Bosnia-Hercegovina. It is "a scandal" that the Croatian 
Government is not keeping its promise, Kohl said today in an 
interview with the private television channel SAT.1. This must 
be met with "the strongest rejection." At the same time, 
however, the chancellor defended the fact that the German 
Government had pressed for the speedy recognition of Croatia and 
Slovenia. Developments in Slovenia are a "success," he said. 

</TEXT>

