<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ahtisaari Elected President in Popular Voting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0602194494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1920 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0602194494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] All the votes have now been counted. About 3.2 
million were cast. Martti Ahtisaari received 53.9 percent -- 
about 1.7 million -- and Elisabeth Rehn received 46.1 percent, 
about 1.4 million. The difference between the candidates is 7.8 
percent; in terms of numbers of votes it is about 250,000. The 
turnout was 82.3 percent. 

</TEXT>

