<F P=106> [Article signed CET: "Europe's Honor and Future At Stake in </F>
Yugoslavia"; as released by Brussels BELGA Database] 
  [Excerpts] Brussels, 07/02 (BELGA) -- "The outside world 
will judge us by our attitude toward former Yugoslavia. We 
cannot exclude a single means of obtaining peace." [Belgian] 
Foreign Affairs Minister Willy Claes said this at the opening of 
the European Council of Foreign Ministers on Monday [7 
February]. [passage omitted] 
  Minister Claes said he hoped the EU would "reach a clearly 
shared position, not just in words, but also in action" where 
"no single avenue is excluded." 
  "As for the values of our civilization, we must hold a 
standard and we no longer have the right to step back," Minister 
Claes stated. 

