<H3> <TI>   Ministers Assure Albania's Bitincka of Continued Support </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0502183594 Tirana ATA in English 1108 GMT 5 Feb 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0502183594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 5 (ATA) -- Albanian minister of 
transports, Fatos Bitincka, has paid a one-day visit to Bonn at 
the invitation of Mr. Wissmann, German minister of transports. 
During the talks, the two sides agreed in principle to sign as 
soon as possible an agreement on roads, goods and passengers and 
a maritime agreement. 
  Mr. Wissmann said that Germany will continue to make its 
contribution to the development of Albanian infrastructure 
through its support for Albania in international organizations. 
  Mr. Bitincka also met with Mr. Schmidtbauer, minister at the 
cabinet of Chancellor Kohl. They focused on the development in 
Albania and the situation in the region. Mr. Schmidtbauer 
assured the Albanian minister of a continuous support by the 
German Government for Albania in the bilateral and multilateral 
aspects and presented some concrete possibilities of short-term, 
mid-term, and long-term cooperation. 
  A working meeting was also held in the German Ministry of 
Foreign Economic Cooperation. 

