<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-026 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Ratifies Cyprus Observer's Appointment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0702221394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2000 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0702221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The European Union's [EU] Ministerial Council 
tonight unanimously approved the appointment of Frenchman Serge 
Abou as EU observer at the talks on the Cyprus issue. He will 
be reporting on the course of the talks and whether they are 
proceeding in accordance with Community norms. 
  Ioannis Kranidhiotis, Greek Foreign Ministry secretary 
general, said that the observer's appointment was accepted by 
the 12 EU ministers with great satisfaction. The proposal for 
Serge Abou's appointment was submitted by Hans van den Broek, EU 
Commissioner in charge of foreign relations. Hans van den Broek 
made it clear that the observer will be following the talks on 
the Cyprus issue as an EU representative, but in his capacity as 
employee of the European Commission, he will submit his reports 
to the competent Commission members. According to our 
correspondent, the Council of Ministers will be free to summon 
the observer for direct briefings or it will be briefed by Hans 
van den Broek. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

