<H3> <TI>   Troops Leave for UN Duty in Eastern Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802122794 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A group of 320 Dutch soldiers left the Netherlands 
today for the Croatian port city of Split. They are to relieve 
the Canadian and Ukrainian UN forces in the Muslim enclaves of 
Srebrenica and Zepce in eastern Bosnia. A total of 1,200 Dutch 
blue berets will be deployed in the enclaves. A group of Dutch 
Army quartermasters in already in the two towns to prepare for 
the troops' arrival. 

