<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aircraft Carrier, Other Warships Head for Adriatic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802091094 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 0700 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alain Juppe defended a strong 
French position in Brussels yesterday. He was supported, in 
particular, by Belgium, the Netherlands, and Italy. 
  According to today's edition of LE FIGARO, three French Navy 
warships, including the aircraft carrier Foch, are to leave 
Toulon in the next few hours to join three other French warships 
already in the Adriatic. The aircraft aboard the Foch -- some 
20 Super Etendard -- would complement the Air Force elements 
made up of Mirage and Jaguar aircraft already based in Italy. 

</TEXT>

