<H3> <TI>   * Finance Minister, Paper View 1994 Budget Proposal </TI></H3>
<H4>   * Machinery for Baltics </H4>
<F P=102> 94EN0194G Stockholm DAGENS NYHETER in Swedish 11 Jan 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94EN0194G </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm DAGENS NYHETER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Road Machinery for Baltic States"] </F>
  [Text] (TT) -- The government is recommending that the 
National Road Administration send surplus equipment to the 
Baltic states. 
  One result of that agency's reorganization was to make 
certain road machines and trucks superfluous. 
  The National Road Administration is selling off its surplus, 
but there is no demand for some of its older equipment. But 
there is a serious lack of that kind of equipment in the Baltic 
states. The government therefore considers it reasonable that 
the National Road Administration should send its unsalable older 
equipment over there. 

</TEXT>

