<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Urges SPD on Amendment on UN Combat Missions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802122194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1105 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel (Free Democratic Party) has forcefully called on the SPD 
[Social Democratic Party] to agree to the participation of the 
Bundeswehr in UN combat missions. Kinkel stressed today in Bonn 
that during yesterday's EU discussions in Brussels on the war in 
Bosnia, he was again forced to experience what it meant to have 
to refer to German constitutional reality in this situation. 
Therefore, the SPD had to give up its "blockade" and agree to 
an appropriate amendment to the Basic Law. 

</TEXT>

