<H3> <TI>   Kohl Wants Coalition To Continue After Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0402145194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1352 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0402145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
stressed that he wishes to continue the Bonn Government 
coalition between the Union parties and the FDP [Free Democratic 
Party] following the Bundestag elections on 16 October this 
year. He would "fight" for this, Kohl said today during an 
interview with the private television station SAT1. He intended 
to conduct and win an "intensive and highly committed election 
campaign." Kohl added he was "not particularly impressed" by 
poor opinion poll results. "The election will be decided on 
polling day," he said. 

</TEXT>

