<H3> <TI>   Bavarian Engineers Plan Token Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702190194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1637 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ingolstadt (DDP/ADN) -- Token strikes are to be 
stepped up in the Bavarian engineering industry over the next 
few days following the interim failure of the pay talks in North 
Rhine-Westphalia. IG Metall spokesman Michael Knuth said in 
Ingolstadt today that token strikes would focus on the Audi 
plant in Ingolstadt as well as further protests in Upper Bavaria 
[southern Bavaria] and the town of Bamberg [northern Bavaria]. 
Staff are planning to leave their places of work and, weather 
permitting, demonstrate on the streets. The union is also 
planning protest action at BMW on Thursday [10 February]. 

</TEXT>

