<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Defends Policy, Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0602210394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1800 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0602210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent Nikoletta Dhoukaki] </F>
  [Excerpt] National Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis 
arrived at Corfu Airport last night at the invitation of the 
PASOK [Panhellenic Socialist Movement] Municipal Committee in 
Kerkira. Arsenis was accompanied by Mrs. Louka Katseli. 
  Speaking at the Municipal Committee's annual meeting, 
Arsenis 
said he is convinced that PASOK will win the two 1994 elections 
and stressed that the government has the willingness and 
experience to deal with the challenge of the Greek presidency 
successfully. Referring to the government's foreign policy, 
Arsenis stressed that Greece will regain its international 
credibility and defend its national rights. 
  [Begin Arsenis recording] We proceeded with courage on the 
Cyprus issue by announcing the joint Greek-Cypriot defensive 
area. Without many words and much publicity, we have passed 
everywhere the message that Greece is not joking, that we--the 
government and the people--are ready to deal with the danger 
from the East because we are not willing to give up even an inch 
of territory, airspace, or sea to Turkey. We will defend our 
national rights. [end recording] 
  Discussing the Armed Forces, the national defense minister 
stressed that they belong to the Greek people and are not to be 
used in anyone's feud. He added that the new law passed by the 
government overturned New Democracy's injustices. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

