<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Send Military Aid to Palestinians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0402163394 Athens ATHENS NEWS in English 4 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0402163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ATHENS NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Greece is to send an estimated one billion drachmas 
worth of military airplanes, helicopters, army trucks, and 
uniforms to help the Palestinians organize a security force in 
accordance with the Israeli-PLO accord signed at the White House 
last year. The offer has been accepted by the Palestinians 
except for six CH-13 helicopters and two U-17AB reconnaissance 
planes, considered to be outdated equipment. 
  Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis and Foreign Minister 
Karolos Papoulias toured Greek army camps inspecting the 
material which will be given free as part of the Greek 
contribution towards peace in the Middle East. PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat made a request for such supplies during a meeting 
with Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou on his recent visit to 
Greece. 

</TEXT>

