<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish-Bosnian Communique Calls For World Assistance </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0702194694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0702194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Turkey and Bosnia-Herzegovina have signed a 
cultural cooperation protocol. The protocol was signed by 
Culture Minister Fikri Saglar and Enest Drakovic, Bosnian 
minister of education, science, and culture. 
  Saglar and Drakovic have also issued a joint communique 
appealing to the world to end the continuing massacre of the 
Bosnian people and the destruction of the Bosnian cultural 
heritage. The communique strongly condemns the international 
community's indifference against the massacre in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Stressing the necessity of implementing all 
the UN Security Council resolutions on Bosnia-Herzegovina, the 
communique asks that the unjust arms embargo be lifted 
immediately. The communique further calls for an end to the 
bombing of the civilian population, the declaration of an 
overall cease-fire, and for NATO to undertake every possible 
military action to prevent Serbian aggression. The communique, 
which is signed by the two ministers, will be sent to 
international organizations including the United Nations and the 
Council of Europe. 
  Drakovic also met with National Defense Minister Nevzat 
Ayaz. 
Ayaz said that Turkey is supporting Bosnia-Herzegovina at 
international platforms and that it will also help solve the 
problems encountered in the field of education. Drakovic 
thanked Turkey for the close interest it has shown and the aid 
it has extended so far. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

