<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Minister Leaves for Economic Talks in Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0702120094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0702120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] State Minister Cemil Erhan has left for Tehran to 
attend the joint economic committee meetings to be held there. 
  In a statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport before his 
departure, Erhan said that last year imports from Iran amounted 
to $590 million, while exports totaled $235 million. 
  Erhan said that during the talks, the two sides will discuss 
ways of increasing exports to Iran, eliminating the delays in 
payment, and the issue of receiving additional crude oil in 
return for goods. He added: We will also discuss border trade, 
the Iran-Turkey-Europe natural gas pipeline, and cooperation in 
the fields of agriculture, petrochemicals, transportation, and 
communications. 
  Erhan will return to Turkey on 10 February. 

</TEXT>

