[EU] member countries today appealed for an emergency NATO 
conference to discuss the immediate lifting of the siege on 
Sarajevo using all necessary means, including air raids. The 
decision was made after last Saturday's [5 February] massacre in 
the market place of the Bosnian capital. 
  Following six hours of talks, the EU foreign ministers 
