<H3> <TI>   Ambassadors To Meet 9 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702175894 Paris AFP in English 1750 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, Feb 7 (AFP) -- NATO ambassadors will 
consider the situation in Sarajevo at their regular weekly 
meeting Wednesday [9 February], rather than call a special 
session, a source close to the North Atlantic Treaty 
Organisation said Monday. 
  This follows a call by EC foreign ministers for the North 
Atlantic Council to consider all possible means, including air 
strikes, to break the 22-month-old siege of Sarajevo by the 
Bosnian Serbs. 

