<H3> <TI>   Canada Expresses Outrage Over Sarajevo Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702135294 Paris AFP in English 2217 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ottawa, Feb 6 (AFP) -- Canada expressed outrage 
Sunday [6 February] over the Sarajevo marketplace attack that 
killed scores of civilians and left nearly 200 injured. 
  Foreign Minister Andre Ouellet described Saturday's attack 
as 
the "deliberate killing and wounding of hundreds of innocent 
civilians." 
  He added, "This latest atrocity underscores the urgent need 
for concerted international action to prevent further violence 
against the innocent civilian population of Sarajevo." 
  Ouellet said he had consulted with U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher and British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd on 
Sunday about a response to the attack. 

</TEXT>

